- change the cost function to penalize depending on where the rest position is and what the target is. This will force the model to 
  move the robot instead of choosing to average out rewards by doing nothing.

Keep:
  Distance reward
  Best distance bonus
  tip speed penalty
Verify:
  Antagonist penalty cancels out actions?
  node speeds penalty, gate it to near-target only (nodes will move when getting to target)
  Correct direction bonus ? Could be right. Should be applied if the tip is far from the target (to not conflict with tip speed penalty)
Choose between:
  Tensions penalty (probably this one) OR Tendon switching penalty

Tensions penalty:
tensions_penalty       → penalizes large Δtension between steps
tendon_switching_penalty → penalizes turning tendons ON/OFF between steps

Turning a tendon from 0 → any value is already a large Δtension, so tensions_penalty already catches tendon switching. Having both means 
switching tendons gets double-penalized, which may be too strong and could cause the agent to freeze its actions entirely — 
potentially explaining why you need the harsh -10.0 all-zeros penalty as a counterweight.

Recommendation: Pick one. tensions_penalty is more nuanced since it scales with the magnitude of change. 
If you keep only that, you can likely also soften or remove the -10.0 all-zeros penalty in tendon_switching_penalty.